sec.p:
The two sets of length-specific temporary POs are defined as:




5′tPO={5′tPOLmin,…,5′tPOLmax}







3′tPO={3′tPOLmin,…,3′tPOLmax}



where Lmin and Lmax are the minimum and the maximum length of the reads, respectively.

Next, to each read (R) mapping on the TIS the temporary POs corresponding to its length is assigned, obtaining two sets of read-specific tPOs:




5′tPOR={5′tPOR1,…,5′tPORN}







3′tPOR={3′tPOR1,…,3′tPORN}



where N is the number of reads mapping on the TIS.
